cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DM, cs.NE 

The paper presents an extended implementation of the Random ferns algorithm for machine learning, which is a popular topic in several sub-categories of computer science. The use of bagging and error approximation is related to machine learning and data mining (cs.DM), while the consumption of categorical and numerical attributes expands the algorithm's applicability to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV) tasks. The benchmarks' results and comparison with Random forest algorithm suggest that the paper is likely to be classified under machine learning (cs.LG) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories.
